asterisk-pjsip-cisco (0.5.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * pjsip cisco status: device facts (MAC, source host, device
    name, firmware loads) now nest inside each Contact #N block
    rather than appearing as a single post-loop block. Multi-
    device endpoints (e.g. one extension with both a LAN and WAN
    phone registered) no longer conflate physical devices.
    cisco_mac_info carries the producing REGISTER's Call-ID;
    matched against ast_sip_contact->call_id at render time.
  * tests: new test_blf_pidf golden-output test for the
    unsolicited-NOTIFY PIDF body builder (extracted to
    res/cisco_unsolicited_blf/pidf.c). Catches body-shape
    regressions before they reach a real Cisco phone. Asterisk-
    API shim under tests/unit/include/asterisk/ + matching
    implementations in tests/unit/asterisk_stubs.c — future
    body-builder helpers can follow the same pattern.
  * conf-samples: extensions.conf.cisco-features.sample grows
    52 -> 195 lines with four CISCO_* dialplan-function recipes
    (CFwdAll softkey capture, DND-aware Dial, CFwdAll-honoring
    Dial, hunt-group bulk toggle). Flags the save-side
    asymmetry — DND / HuntGroup are auto-captured server-side,
    CFwdAll requires dialplan to catch the phone's service-URI
    INVITE.
  * No API or sorcery-schema change; drop-in over v0.5.0.

 -- Andrew Simmonds <simmo@rinseout.org>  Mon, 18 May 2026 17:00:00 +0800

asterisk-pjsip-cisco (0.5.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New `pjsip cisco status <endpoint>` CLI: one-shot dump of
    sorcery config, registration state, MWI counts, REGISTER
    Call-ID, harvested MAC, and the device's self-reported
    firmware active / inactive load. Multi-line aliases handled
    via the lifted cisco_mac_* shared API.
  * REGISTER Reason-header parsing: DeviceName / ActiveLoadId /
    InactiveLoadId stored on the MAC-keyed device map and
    surfaced via the status CLI.
  * res_pjsip_cisco_remotecc: split unsolicited-alarm and
    remotecc-response log paths so a noisy alarm phone doesn't
    drown out response-flow diagnostics.
  * Tree refactor to Asterisk house style: per-module
    subdirectories under res/, public headers under
    include/cisco/, build outputs under obj/. Output paths
    parameterised via OBJ_DIR / MODULE_BUILD_DIR / DOC_XML.
    No ABI or sorcery-schema change — installs as a drop-in
    replacement for v0.4.2.
  * tests/unit: libxml2-linked test_xml_bodies parses every
    sprintf'd wire-format body template; CI gains a module-load
    smoke step that loads all ten .so files against apt's
    Asterisk when the major version matches the build matrix.

 -- Andrew Simmonds <simmo@rinseout.org>  Mon, 18 May 2026 12:00:00 +0800

asterisk-pjsip-cisco (0.4.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Phantom video suppression now also fires when the call
    terminates in Asterisk (MusicOnHold, VoiceMail, IVR,
    ConfBridge meet-me, dialplan apps). v0.4.0 covered the
    video-phone -> voice-only-SIP-endpoint case but missed the
    "no second SIP leg at all" case, leaving black video panes
    on calls to e.g. *97 voicemail or hold-music extensions.
    Fixed by counting only PJSIP-tech siblings in the linkedid
    walk and treating zero PJSIP siblings as "no video sink ->
    suppress".
  * Bench-verified on Asterisk 22.9 against CP-8865 dialing
    MusicOnHold and SayUnixTime extensions.

 -- Andrew Simmonds <simmo@rinseout.org>  Sat, 16 May 2026 12:00:00 +0800

asterisk-pjsip-cisco (0.4.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Docs-only: trim conf-samples/extensions.conf.cisco-features.sample
