asterisk-pjsip-cisco (0.4.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * H.264 imageattr propagation across the bridge: incoming SDP
    imageattr stashed on the receiving leg's ast_channel, mirrored
    onto the bridge peer's outgoing answer (replaces static fallback).
    Two-phase peer find handles both post-bridge (ast_channel_bridge_peer)
    and pre-bridge (linkedid walk with aggregation) lookups.
  * Phantom video answer suppression: when a video phone dials a
    voice-only endpoint, the answer's m=video stream is now rejected
    with port=0 instead of leaving the caller's video pane open
    waiting for frames that never arrive. Aggregation across
    linkedid candidates skips helper channels with no datastore.
  * Conference bridge video mode: Confrn and Join now call
    ast_bridge_set_*_video_mode() on the multimix bridge, auto-
    picking SINGLE_SRC (one video peer) or TALKER_SRC (multi-video)
    based on participant capability. Fixes black-video in Confrn'd
    door-camera-into-mobile calls.
  * Internals: res_pjsip_cisco_conference.c split into focused
    sibling files (cisco_conf_state.c, cisco_conf_list.c,
    cisco_conf_confrn.c) sharing declarations via cisco_conference.h.
  * Tooling: make tests target with smoke (xmllint + readelf
    symbol checks on every .so) and pjlib-linked unit harness.
    Smoke wired into CI; expanded -W* hardening flags applied
    across the codebase (clean on 20.x / 22.x / 23.x).
  * Bench-debugged against CP-8865 + CP-8861 + CP-7975 + 2N IP Verso
    door intercom on Asterisk 22.9.

 -- Andrew Simmonds <simmo@rinseout.org>  Fri, 15 May 2026 23:30:46 +0800

asterisk-pjsip-cisco (0.3.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Conference Phase 1: Confrn-built multimix bridge with phone-side
    UI promotion (holdretrievereq + Cisco-flavoured in-dialog NOTIFY +
    Event:refer NOTIFY), ConfList read + Mute/Remove/Update action
    softkeys, Join/Select/Unselect multi-call merge, RmLastConf, and
    cisco_keep_conference for initiator-hangup behaviour.
  * DND / CFwdALL / HuntGroup CLIs and CISCO_*() dialplan functions;
    writes also push a bulkupdate REFER so phone-side UI updates in
    real time. DND additionally drives BLF lamps via a Cisco
    presence-state provider.
  * Record softkey (StartRecording / StopRecording) via MixMonitor on
    the bridged channel.
  * pjsip cisco prt-report CLI.
  * Internals: helper bodies moved into res_pjsip_cisco_endpoint.so as
    shared symbols; NAT'd-contact RURI rewrite globalised as an
    on_tx_request hook so REFER + NOTIFY both pick it up.
  * Bench-tested against Asterisk 20.19, 22.9, and 23.3.

 -- Andrew Simmonds <simmo@rinseout.org>  Fri, 15 May 2026 11:41:26 +0800

asterisk-pjsip-cisco (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release — early 0.x; wants real-world testing before 1.0.
  * Ten shared modules: res_pjsip_cisco_{endpoint,
    pidf_body_generator, register_optionsind, bulkupdate,
    unsolicited_blf, service_control, feature_events, call_extras,
    remotecc, conference}.
  * Built and CI'd against Asterisk 20.x / 22.x / 23.x; bench-tested
    against a Cisco 7975 running Enterprise SIP firmware 9.4.2 on
    Asterisk 22.9.0.

